comment.author: 35234565@N04
comment._content: Thanks so much swanq for finding such great images of the Univ. of Wash. crew team in 1914. What's throwing me however, is the location of this shot. 2FunAdGuyz is selling a poster showing a crew team lifting their shell out of or into the water at what appears to be the same location as this Bain image. www.the2funadguyz.com/unwi19rocrpo.html They label the team, perhaps incorrectly, Univ. of Wisconsin varsity rowing team, on the Hudson River near Poughkeepsie. Not to say that the team shown isn't the 1914 Washington Huskies, but all I can nail down for sure is the bridge.
